text: I think we're seeing the market start to price that in a little bit more as of late, especially with what's going on right now. Right now is September 2nd, and we're seeing volatility move in relation with spot. So that's a little bit different. But I think the actual real outliers, I think, are still underpriced. I think people aren't giving as much credence to some of the two to three standard deviation moves as they should be right now. And I'm also a believer that markets don't fall apart when everybody's anticipating them to fall apart. It just doesn't work that way. It's an effect that happens when everybody doesn't see it coming. That's when the unraveling effect takes place. So we really hold a belief that you're not going to be able to sit there and time this. Of course. Of course, as with every volatility trader, we have our quote unquote like GARC models that we kind of throw out the window because I don't truly believe that anybody could accurately estimate in time when you'll get that massive volatility spike. But what you can do is you can structure yourself around it. And that's how we kind of view vol is we're going to look for the best play that presents itself out there and structure the book around that.
